## Phase 4: Distroless Docker Images

This is where many developers get confused because Distroless looks similar to Alpine, but its goal is different.

---

## First understand the problem

Current runtime image:

```dockerfile
FROM node:20-alpine
```

Contains:

```text
Node.js
Alpine Linux
Shell (sh)
Package manager
Linux utilities
```

You can do:

```bash
docker exec -it backend sh
```

and get inside.

---

### Security problem

If an attacker gets access to your container:

```text
Shell available
+
Linux commands available
+
Utilities available
```

makes it easier to move around inside the container.

---

## Distroless idea

Google created Distroless images.

Instead of:

```text
Node
+
Linux OS
+
Shell
+
Utilities
```

you get:

```text
Node
+
Only required runtime libraries
```

Nothing extra.

---

## Think of it this way

### Alpine

```text
House
├── Bedroom
├── Kitchen
├── Hall
└── Bathroom
```

### Distroless

```text
Tiny room
└── Only what you need
```

---

## Practical Example

Create:

```dockerfile
FROM node:20 AS builder

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install

COPY . .

FROM gcr.io/distroless/nodejs20-debian12

WORKDIR /app

COPY --from=builder /app .

CMD ["app.js"]
```

Notice:

```dockerfile
CMD ["app.js"]
```

not:

```dockerfile
CMD ["node","app.js"]
```

because Node is already the entrypoint.

---

## Build

```bash
docker build -t backend:distroless .
```

Run:

```bash
docker run -d \
--name backend-distroless \
-p 3000:3000 \
backend:distroless
```

---

## Test

Try:

```bash
docker exec -it backend-distroless sh
```

Result:

```text
Error
```

No shell exists.

That's expected.

---

## Compare

| Feature                    | Node | Alpine | Distroless |
| -------------------------- | ---- | ------ | ---------- |
| Runs app                   | ✅    | ✅      | ✅          |
| Shell                      | ✅    | ✅      | ❌          |
| Package manager            | ✅    | ✅      | ❌          |
| Debugging inside container | ✅    | ✅      | ❌          |
| Smaller attack surface     | ❌    | ⚠️     | ✅          |
| Production usage           | ⚠️   | ✅      | ✅✅         |

---

## When should you use Distroless?

Good for:

```text
Production
Kubernetes
Swarm
Microservices
APIs
```

Avoid while learning/debugging because:

```bash
docker exec -it container sh
```

won't work.

---

## Real-world flow

Most companies:

```text
Development
↓
node:20

Testing
↓
node:20-alpine

Production
↓
Distroless
```

---

## Practical task

Create a new Dockerfile:

```dockerfile
FROM node:20 AS builder

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install

COPY . .

FROM gcr.io/distroless/nodejs20-debian12

WORKDIR /app

COPY --from=builder /app .

CMD ["app.js"]
```

Then:

```bash
docker build -t backend:distroless .
docker run -d --name distroless-app -p 4000:3000 backend:distroless
docker ps
docker logs distroless-app
docker exec -it distroless-app sh
```

Observe:

1. App runs normally.
2. Logs work normally.
3. `docker exec ... sh` fails.

That's the key lesson of Distroless.

After you complete that, move to **Phase 5: Swarm Overlay Network**, where you'll learn how containers on different Swarm nodes communicate using a virtual network.


