## Distroless:-
keerthana@Keerthanas-MacBook-Air multi-stage-build % docker exec -it backend-distroless sh
OCI runtime exec failed: exec failed: unable to start container process: exec: "sh": executable file not found in $PATH: unknown

The error:

```bash
docker exec -it backend-distroless sh
```

returns:

```bash
exec: "sh": executable file not found in $PATH
```

because inside the Distroless container:

```text
/bin/sh ❌
/bin/bash ❌
apt ❌
apk ❌
curl ❌
ping ❌
```

don't exist.

Normal image:

```text
Container
 ├── Node
 ├── Shell (sh)
 ├── Package Manager
 ├── OS Tools
 └── App
```

Distroless image:

```text
Container
 ├── Node
 └── App
```

Nothing extra.

That's why attackers cannot easily:

```bash
docker exec -it container sh
```

and start exploring the container.

---

You can verify the application is running using:

```bash
docker ps
```

If it shows:

```text
STATUS: Up
```

then the Node application started successfully.

You can also test:

```bash
curl localhost:3000
```

or open:

```text
http://localhost:3000
```

from your browser.

---

## One-line: -
Multi-stage build reduces unnecessary files.
Distroless removes shell and OS utilities.
Smaller attack surface.
More secure production image.

*One-line definition:*
Distroless images contain only the application runtime and required files, removing shells and operating-system tools to improve security and reduce image size.